aa(lp197
VWhat other properties of language does the script show?
p198
aVLanguages contain patterns.
p199
aVIf I give you the letter Q
p200
aVand ask you to predict the next letter, what do you think that would be?
p201
aVMost of you said U, which is right.
p202
aVNow if I asked you to predict one more letter,
p203
aVwhat do you think that would be?
p204
aVNow there's several thoughts. There's E. It could be I. It could be A,
p205
aVbut certainly not B, C or D, right?
p206
aVThe Indus script also exhibits similar kinds of patterns.
p207
aVThere's a lot of text that start with this diamond-shaped symbol.
p208
aVAnd this in turn tends to be followed
p209
aVby this quotation marks-like symbol.
p210
aVAnd this is very similar to a Q and U example.
p211
aVThis symbol can in turn be followed
p212
aVby these fish-like symbols and some other signs,
p213
aVbut never by these other signs at the bottom.
p214
aVAnd furthermore, there's some signs
p215
aVthat really prefer the end of texts,
p216
aVsuch as this jar-shaped sign,
p217
aVand this sign, in fact, happens to be
p218
aVthe most frequently occurring sign in the script.
