aVGiven the computer model,
p228
aVwe can test the model by essentially quizzing it.
p229
aVSo we could deliberately erase some symbols,
p230
aVand we can ask it to predict the missing symbols.
p231
aVHere are some examples.
p232
aVYou may regard this
p233
aVas perhaps the most ancient game
p234
aVof Wheel of Fortune.
p235
aa(lp236
VWhat we found
p237
aVwas that the computer was successful in 75 percent of the cases
p238
aVin predicting the correct symbol.
p239
aVIn the rest of the cases,
p240
aVtypically the second best guess or third best guess was the right answer.
p241
aVThere's also practical use
p242
aVfor this particular procedure.
p243
aVThere's a lot of these texts that are damaged.
p244
aVHere's an example of one such text.
p245
aVAnd we can use the computer model now to try to complete this text
p246
aVand make a best guess prediction.
p247
aVHere's an example of a symbol that was predicted.
